summary: This FBI document details an attempt by agents from the Palm Springs Resident Agency to interview Alfredo Rodriguez regarding an obstruction of justice investigation. Rodriguez refused to be interviewed, citing a non-disclosure agreement signed in reference to Jeffrey Epstein. The document indicates Rodriguez had moved to the Philippines.

events.title: FBI Attempts to Interview Alfredo Rodriguez
events.description: FBI agents from the Palm Springs Resident Agency attempted to interview Alfredo Rodriguez at his residence in California regarding an obstruction of justice investigation. He was not home, but later refused an interview by phone, citing a non-disclosure agreement related to Jeffrey Epstein.

keyFacts: FBI agents attempted to interview Alfredo Rodriguez as part of an obstruction of justice investigation (Case ID 72-MM-I13327).
Alfredo Rodriguez refused to be interviewed, citing a non-disclosure agreement he had signed in reference to Jeffrey Epstein.
The document indicates Alfredo Rodriguez had moved to the Philippines.
The investigation was being handled by the Palm Springs Resident Agency with coordination through the Miami field office.
